  "lesson_key": "circles-ellipses",
  "title": "Circles and Ellipses",
  "content": "<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Circle</strong></strong> Equations on the Coordinate Plane</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">A circle is all points that are the same <strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">distance</strong></strong> (<strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">radius</strong></strong>) from a center point. On the coordinate plane, we can write this as an equation!</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Standard Form of a Circle</h4>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.2rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 2px solid #3b82f6; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>(x − h)² + (y − k)² = r²</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>(h, k)</strong> = center of the circle</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>r</strong> = radius of the circle</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>r²</strong> = radius squared (what appears on the right side)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"420\" viewBox=\"-10 -10 420 440\">\n  <defs>\n    <pattern id=\"grid-circle\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" patternUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n      <path d=\"M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/>\n    </pattern>\n  </defs>\n  <rect width=\"400\" height=\"400\" fill=\"url(#grid-circle)\"/>\n  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"200\" x2=\"400\" y2=\"200\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"400\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <circle cx=\"280\" cy=\"160\" r=\"80\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <circle cx=\"280\" cy=\"160\" r=\"4\" fill=\"#ef4444\"/>\n  <text x=\"295\" y=\"155\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#ef4444\">(h, k)</text>\n  <line x1=\"280\" y1=\"160\" x2=\"360\" y2=\"160\" stroke=\"#10b981\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-dasharray=\"3,3\"/>\n  <text x=\"320\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#10b981\">r</text>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"430\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">(x − h)² + (y − k)² = r²</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">💡 Key Pattern:</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">The signs in the equation tell you the center! If you see (x − 3)², the center x-coordinate is +3. If you see (x + 2)², the center x-coordinate is −2. The signs flip!</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 1: Finding Center and Radius</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> What is the center and radius of the circle (x − 5)² + (y + 2)² = 16?</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Compare to (x − h)² + (y − k)² = r²<br><br>\n  (x − 5)² means h = 5 ✓<br>\n  (y + 2)² means (y − (−2))², so k = −2 ✓<br>\n  r² = 16, so r = 4 ✓<br><br>\n  <strong>Center: (5, −2)</strong><br>\n  <strong>Radius: 4</strong>\n</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 2: Writing Circle Equation</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> Write the equation of a circle with center (−3, 1) and radius 7.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Use (x − h)² + (y − k)² = r²<br>\n  h = −3, k = 1, r = 7<br><br>\n  (x − (−3))² + (y − 1)² = 7²<br>\n  <strong>(x + 3)² + (y − 1)² = 49</strong>\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Completing the Square</strong></strong></h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">Sometimes circle equations aren't in standard form. You'll need to <strong>complete the square</strong> to find the center and radius.</p>\n\n\n  <p style=\"font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; color: #92400e; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">📝 Steps to Complete the Square:</p>\n  <ol style=\"margin: 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; color: #78350f;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">Group x terms and y terms separately</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">Take half of the x coefficient, square it, add to both sides</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">Take half of the y coefficient, square it, add to both sides</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">Factor each perfect square</li>\n  </ol>\n\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 3: Completing the Square</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> Convert x² + y² − 4x + 6y + 9 = 0 to standard form.</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Step 1: Group x and y terms<br>\n  (x² − 4x) + (y² + 6y) = −9<br><br>\n  Step 2: Complete the square for x<br>\n  Half of −4 is −2, square it: (−2)² = 4<br>\n  (x² − 4x + 4) + (y² + 6y) = −9 + 4<br><br>\n  Step 3: Complete the square for y<br>\n  Half of 6 is 3, square it: 3² = 9<br>\n  (x² − 4x + 4) + (y² + 6y + 9) = −9 + 4 + 9<br><br>\n  Step 4: Factor<br>\n  <strong>(x − 2)² + (y + 3)² = 4</strong><br><br>\n  Center: (2, −3), Radius: 2\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Ellipse</strong></strong> Basics</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">An <strong>ellipse</strong> is a stretched circle. It has two axes: a longer one (major axis) and a shorter one (minor axis).</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Standard Form of an Ellipse</h4>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 2px solid #9333ea; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>(x − h)²/a² + (y − k)²/b² = 1</strong>\n</p>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>(h, k)</strong> = center of the ellipse</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>a</strong> = semi-major axis (longer radius)</li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>b</strong> = semi-minor axis (shorter radius)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"450\" height=\"200\" viewBox=\"0 0 450 200\">\n  <text x=\"225\" y=\"40\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-weight=\"bold\">x² + 6x + 9 = (x + 3)²</text>\n  <rect x=\"50\" y=\"80\" width=\"80\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <text x=\"90\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#2563eb\" text-anchor=\"middle\">x²</text>\n  <rect x=\"140\" y=\"80\" width=\"40\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#fef3c7\" stroke=\"#f59e0b\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <text x=\"160\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#f59e0b\" text-anchor=\"middle\">3x</text>\n  <rect x=\"190\" y=\"80\" width=\"40\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#fef3c7\" stroke=\"#f59e0b\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <text x=\"210\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#f59e0b\" text-anchor=\"middle\">3x</text>\n  <rect x=\"240\" y=\"80\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" fill=\"#d1fae5\" stroke=\"#10b981\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <text x=\"260\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#10b981\" text-anchor=\"middle\">9</text>\n  <text x=\"320\" y=\"130\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"24\" fill=\"#000\">=</text>\n  <rect x=\"360\" y=\"80\" width=\"80\" height=\"80\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <text x=\"400\" y=\"175\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"14\" fill=\"#2563eb\" text-anchor=\"middle\">(x+3)²</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Example 4: Ellipse Center and Axes</h4>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\"><strong>Problem:</strong> What is the center of the ellipse (x − 1)²/25 + (y + 2)²/9 = 1?</p>\n\n<p style=\"padding: 1rem;  border-left: 3px solid #10b981; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>Solution:</strong><br>\n  Compare to (x − h)²/a² + (y − k)²/b² = 1<br><br>\n  (x − 1)² means h = 1<br>\n  (y + 2)² means k = −2<br><br>\n  <strong>Center: (1, −2)</strong><br>\n  Note: a² = 25 so a = 5, b² = 9 so b = 3\n</p>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong style=\"color: #2563eb; text-decoration: underline;\">Hyperbola</strong></strong> Basics (Brief Overview)</h3>\n\n<p style=\" margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">A <strong>hyperbola</strong> has two separate curves that open outward. The equation looks similar to an ellipse, but with a minus sign.</p>\n\n<h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">Standard Form of a Hyperbola</h4>\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; padding: 1rem;  border: 2px solid #dc2626; border-radius: 8px; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;\">\n  <strong>(x − h)²/a² − (y − k)²/b² = 1</strong> (opens left-right)<br>\n  or<br>\n  <strong>(y − k)²/a² − (x − h)²/b² = 1</strong> (opens up-down)\n</p>\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 2rem 0;\">\n<svg width=\"400\" height=\"400\" viewBox=\"-10 -10 420 420\">\n  <defs>\n    <pattern id=\"grid-hyp\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" patternUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n      <path d=\"M 40 0 L 0 0 0 40\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#e5e7eb\" stroke-width=\"0.5\"/>\n    </pattern>\n  </defs>\n  <rect width=\"400\" height=\"400\" fill=\"url(#grid-hyp)\"/>\n  <line x1=\"0\" y1=\"200\" x2=\"400\" y2=\"200\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <line x1=\"200\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"200\" y2=\"400\" stroke=\"#000\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n  <path d=\"M 260 60 Q 280 100 290 140 T 310 200 T 330 260 T 350 320\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <path d=\"M 140 60 Q 120 100 110 140 T 90 200 T 70 260 T 50 320\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#2563eb\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n  <text x=\"200\" y=\"380\" font-family=\"Times New Roman, serif\" font-size=\"16\" fill=\"#000\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Two separate curves</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\n<ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">🔑 Quick Recognition:</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">Circle:  x² + y² (both positive, same coefficients)</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">Ellipse:  x²/a² + y²/b² = 1 (both positive, different denominators)</span></li>\n  <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><span style=\"color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;\">Hyperbola:  x²/a² − y²/b² = 1 (one is negative!)</span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3 style=\"margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\">Summary Table</h3>\n\n<table style=\"width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-size: 0.85rem;\">\n  <tr style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e7eb;\">\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.8rem;\">Shape</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.8rem;\">Equation</th>\n    <th style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; text-align: left; font-weight: 600; color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.8rem;\">Center</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Circle</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">(x−h)² + (y−k)² = r²</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">(h, k)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Ellipse</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">(x−h)²/a² + (y−k)²/b² = 1</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">(h, k)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">Hyperbola</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #374151;\">(x−h)²/a² − (y−k)²/b² = 1</td>\n    <td style=\"padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem; color: #6b7280;\">(h, k)</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">✓ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">✓ Circle: (x−h)² + (y−k)² = r²</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">✓ Signs flip: (x−3) means center x = 3, (y+2) means center y = −2</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">✓ Complete the square to convert to standard form</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">✓ Ellipse has +, Hyperbola has − (minus sign!)</li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\">✓ Center is always (h, k) for all conic sections</li>\n  </ul>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">✓ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Circle equation: (x−h)² + (y−k)² = r²</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Center is (h, k) and radius is r</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Ellipse: (x−h)²/a² + (y−k)²/b² = 1</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Hyperbola has a MINUS sign between squared terms</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Complete the square to convert general form to standard form</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n\n\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">✓ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Circle equation: (x−h)² + (y−k)² = r²</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Center is (h, k) and radius is r</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Ellipse: (x−h)²/a² + (y−k)²/b² = 1</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Hyperbola has a MINUS sign between squared terms</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Complete the square to convert general form to standard form</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n\n<div style=\"background: #f0fdf4; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; border-radius: 8px; margin: 3rem 0 2rem 0; border-left: 4px solid #10b981;\">\n  <h4 style=\"margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\">✓ Key Takeaways</h4>\n  <ul style=\" margin: 1rem 0; padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 2;\">\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Circle equation: (x−h)² + (y−k)² = r²</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Center is (h, k) and radius is r</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Ellipse: (x−h)²/a² + (y−k)²/b² = 1</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Hyperbola has a MINUS sign between squared terms</strong></li>\n    <li style=\" margin: 0.4rem 0;\"><strong>Complete the square to convert general form to standard form</strong></li>\n  </ul>\n</div>",
